<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 30 at 6:52PM CDT until April 30 at 11:00PM CDT by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 730 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN NEVADA AND NORTHERN COLUMBIA COUNTIES...
At 651 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near McNeil, moving
northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Magnolia, Waldo, McNeil, Young, College Hill, Lamartine, Laughlin and
Medlock.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
